<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,823,1101]" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galileo &amp; Martins" authorityYear="2006" box="[151,347,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Eburodacrys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ayri">
<emphasis box="[151,347,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">Eburodacrys ayri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from “ 
<collectingCountry box="[594,709,823,848]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">Colômbia</collectingCountry>
, Rio 
<collectingRegion box="[770,900,823,848]" country="Colombia" name="Magdalena" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">Magdalena</collectingRegion>
.” The 
<collectingRegion box="[973,1098,823,848]" country="Colombia" name="Magdalena" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">Magdalena</collectingRegion>
River is more than 1,500 Km long, it originates in the southwest of 
<collectingCountry box="[589,699,860,885]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and in its route crosses the country from the south to the north, through 18 Colombian departments; therefore, the 
<typeStatus box="[759,807,896,920]" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">type</typeStatus>
locality is inaccurate. Until now, that was the only information about the locality of the species. Herein, the species is registered from the department of 
<collectingRegion box="[1350,1432,932,957]" country="Colombia" name="Tolima" pageId="15" pageNumber="508">Tolima</collectingRegion>
, located in the west-central part of the country.
</paragraph>
